11:20.418 --> 11:22.203
- Yes, come in.

11:22.246 --> 11:24.031
Thank God you're here.

11:24.074 --> 11:26.033
They're medicating
him now--Julian.

11:26.076 --> 11:27.556
They're sedating him.

11:27.599 --> 11:29.732
I'm trying to get a court order
to get them to stop.

11:29.776 --> 11:32.474
And I'm sure you heard
that his confession

11:32.517 --> 11:36.434
is admissible in court,
so that's perfect timing.

11:36.478 --> 11:39.394
What is that?
- I think you know.

11:39.437 --> 11:41.396
Carmen Bell.

11:41.439 --> 11:43.572
It's her deposition.

11:43.615 --> 11:46.923
It was missing from
town records until yesterday.

11:54.626 --> 11:55.932
- Will you please
state your name

11:55.976 --> 11:57.499
and the date
for the record, please?

11:57.542 --> 11:59.240
- My name is Carmen Bell.

11:59.283 --> 12:02.156
The date
is February 20, 2002.

12:03.200 --> 12:04.680
- Oh, my God.

12:04.724 --> 12:06.769
- And how did you end up
in Mosswood Grove?

12:06.813 --> 12:09.250
- Vera Walker.
Uh, she recruited me.

12:09.293 --> 12:13.254
I was working at this
pretzel place at the mall,

12:13.297 --> 12:15.038
and she came in one day.

12:15.082 --> 12:17.432
I was going
through a bad time,

12:17.475 --> 12:20.348
and she just talked to me.

12:20.391 --> 12:21.436
- Okay.

12:21.479 --> 12:23.264
- Told me about Mosswood.

12:23.307 --> 12:27.094
She said it was like a family,
that it would solve things.

12:27.137 --> 12:29.487
We did these sessions, um,

12:29.531 --> 12:32.273
like therapy, I guess.

12:32.316 --> 12:34.057
We would play out

12:34.101 --> 12:36.756
what had happened to us
with each other

12:36.799 --> 12:40.107
until the Beacon,
the--the leader of the place--

12:40.150 --> 12:42.065
he, um...

12:42.109 --> 12:44.285
- It's okay.
Just take your time.

12:44.328 --> 12:46.113
- Stop.
I don't want to hear this.

12:46.156 --> 12:47.636
- I bet you don't.

12:47.679 --> 12:49.246
- He had this epiphany

12:49.290 --> 12:52.075
while he was swimming
at the purple lake.

12:52.119 --> 12:54.817
That's what he called
Stillwater Reservoir--

12:54.861 --> 12:56.471
the purple lake.

12:56.514 --> 12:58.821
He said that the only way
to break out of trauma

12:58.865 --> 13:01.911
was by going
straight into it.

13:01.955 --> 13:04.479
And the sessions
got violent,

13:04.522 --> 13:06.611
physically and sexually.

13:06.655 --> 13:09.919
- Is that how you got
the burns on your foot?

13:09.963 --> 13:11.965
Can you please show us
the burns on your foot?

13:12.008 --> 13:14.924
♪

13:14.968 --> 13:17.666
- One of the men--
he did it in a session.

13:17.709 --> 13:19.842
I-I don't know his name.

13:19.886 --> 13:23.280
Uh, and he kept asking for me.

13:23.324 --> 13:26.675
And there was
another man, and--

13:29.721 --> 13:32.681
And I got pregnant, and

13:32.724 --> 13:35.989
Vera's the one who took me
to Dr. Poole to fix me.

13:36.032 --> 13:37.599
- Get out!

13:37.642 --> 13:40.689
♪

13:40.732 --> 13:43.866
- If Julian was afraid
of anything,

13:43.910 --> 13:45.694
it was probably you.

13:45.737 --> 13:49.350
- I have done everything
I can do to protect him.

13:49.393 --> 13:53.006
- There were abuses
all over Mosswood.

13:53.049 --> 13:54.355
