16:07.923 --> 16:10.708
- Because he told me.

16:12.058 --> 16:14.538
- May I speak to you
for a moment?

16:14.582 --> 16:16.497
- She complained
about a scrape?

16:16.540 --> 16:18.499
- No, I noticed.
- Scrapes heal.

16:18.542 --> 16:23.025
And now Vic, he'll also heal.
That's the point of this.

16:23.069 --> 16:24.331
- It's just--it's--

16:24.374 --> 16:26.333
it's at her expense,
though, isn't it?

16:26.376 --> 16:28.509
- No, Bess needed that moment
just as much as Vic did.

16:28.552 --> 16:30.337
She can go
if she isn't committed.

16:30.380 --> 16:32.121
- Commitment
is not the issue.

16:39.955 --> 16:42.044
♪

16:42.088 --> 16:44.873
Something's happened to you.

16:44.916 --> 16:47.049
- I just keep thinking,

16:47.093 --> 16:49.530
what we're doing,
it's become so literal.

16:49.573 --> 16:51.097
We used to do imaginative work,

16:51.140 --> 16:55.579
and now we're reenacting
our pain on each other.

16:57.233 --> 16:59.975
So you want to go back
to the way things were.

17:00.019 --> 17:02.238
♪

17:02.282 --> 17:05.372
