22:15.769 --> 22:17.858
Come on.
Come here.

22:21.601 --> 22:25.082
♪

22:25.126 --> 22:27.563
- All right,
let's settle down.

22:45.581 --> 22:47.757
- Yeah, I'm headed
up to the cabin tonight.

22:47.801 --> 22:51.065
I need some... space to think.

22:51.108 --> 22:53.937
Much to prepare for.

22:53.981 --> 22:56.940
- Okay.

22:56.984 --> 22:59.900
- Marin struggled last night.

22:59.943 --> 23:02.206
- She wasn't ready.
- Well, she needs to assist.

23:02.250 --> 23:03.425
It'll prepare her.

23:03.469 --> 23:04.774
I want her to
work with Glen tonight.

23:04.818 --> 23:07.037
See to it that it happens.

23:08.996 --> 23:12.129
How's Julian?
- Good.

23:12.173 --> 23:15.959
- Yes, I think so.

23:16.003 --> 23:18.135
- That boy's gonna
change everything.

23:18.179 --> 23:19.615
You'll see.

23:22.662 --> 23:29.712
♪

24:00.526 --> 24:03.267
Where's the Beacon?
- He canceled the work tonight.

24:05.139 --> 24:06.488
We spoke about a session.

24:06.532 --> 24:08.621
I told him
I was bringing people.

24:08.664 --> 24:10.361
- He's reconsidering
the path of the work.

24:10.405 --> 24:11.841
That's all I can say.

24:11.885 --> 24:14.496
♪

24:14.540 --> 24:16.498
- I'm gonna need to
speak to him.

24:16.542 --> 24:18.500
- He's occupied.
- I don't give a shit.

24:18.544 --> 24:20.371
- He's not even on the grounds.

24:20.415 --> 24:24.027
- Who the fuck
do you think you are?

24:24.071 --> 24:28.205
You think you speak for him now?

24:28.249 --> 24:30.512
I was here from the beginning.

24:30.556 --> 24:32.079
I sold him this piece of land--

24:32.122 --> 24:34.603
- And I'm sure he's grateful.

24:36.736 --> 24:39.216
This is bullshit.

24:39.260 --> 24:41.044
Let's go.

24:41.088 --> 24:42.698
Bullshit!

24:42.742 --> 24:48.835
♪

24:53.579 --> 24:55.537
- Shh, shh.

24:59.280 --> 25:00.890
Can you hand me that towel?

25:00.934 --> 25:02.501
- Yeah.

25:02.544 --> 25:06.635
- Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

25:07.593 --> 25:10.073
Thank you.

25:13.468 --> 25:16.079
Who's my little boy?

25:22.869 --> 25:24.653
- Shh, shh, shh.
- Um.

25:24.697 --> 25:26.699
- It just happened.

25:26.742 --> 25:30.006
We thought it would be
better than just formula.

25:30.050 --> 25:32.835
Shh.

25:32.879 --> 25:34.924
Why don't you hold him?

25:34.968 --> 25:37.100
Hmm?

25:40.234 --> 25:42.236
You haven't seen him all day.

25:45.848 --> 25:47.894
Come on.

25:47.937 --> 25:51.767
- Why'd you shut down
the work last night?

25:51.811 --> 25:53.726
Why'd you do that?

25:53.769 --> 25:56.206
- Marin wasn't ready.
She's still recovering.

25:56.250 --> 25:58.600
- I told you what I wanted.

25:58.644 --> 26:00.950
Do you realize what--

26:00.994 --> 26:03.126
Shut up.
You have jeopardized--

26:03.170 --> 26:04.214
Shut up--

26:04.258 --> 26:07.261
- Shh, shh, shh, it's okay.

26:09.785 --> 26:13.136
All right, I am seeing too much
attachment here, far too much.

26:13.180 --> 26:14.921
You need to stop caring
for him.

26:14.964 --> 26:16.618
- He's still breastfeeding.
- I don't care.

26:16.662 --> 26:18.577
Move his basket up to my study,
all his things.

26:18.620 --> 26:20.056
He's staying with me
from now on.

26:20.100 --> 26:21.797
- We have to come in there
to feed him and change him.

26:21.841 --> 26:23.625
He'll keep you up all night.
- I don't care.

26:23.669 --> 26:26.628
- No--
- It won't be much longer now.

26:33.026 --> 26:40.250
♪

27:10.890 --> 27:14.937
- My apology, tea.

27:25.731 --> 27:27.602
- Hm.

27:35.697 --> 27:42.182
♪

27:42.225 --> 27:44.488
- I allowed
horrible things to happen.

27:44.532 --> 27:47.187
I did.

27:47.230 --> 27:50.364
But I did it
because I believed in him,

27:50.407 --> 27:52.758
and he healed me.

27:52.801 --> 27:55.717
♪

27:55.761 --> 27:59.765
I wish I had stopped it
sooner, but I...

28:03.072 --> 28:07.555
When I saw Julian's face,
I woke up.

28:07.598 --> 28:09.035
And I knew what I had to do,

28:09.078 --> 28:12.386
and I changed Mosswood for good.

28:12.429 --> 28:13.866
And I know now that I will

28:13.909 --> 28:18.131
never lose myself
that way ever again.

28:21.395 --> 28:25.878
They just followed you?

28:25.921 --> 28:27.749
- Deep down, there were
many of us who were

28:27.793 --> 28:30.317
uneasy about
where we were headed.

28:31.797 --> 28:35.583
- Your Beacon,
what happened to him?

28:37.280 --> 28:40.240
He was unhappy for a long time.

28:40.283 --> 28:43.069
One day he left us.

28:43.112 --> 28:46.159
Didn't say good-bye, nothing.

28:49.815 --> 28:54.428
I had no idea
Carmen pursued legal action.

28:54.471 --> 28:57.910
- It was never filed.

28:57.953 --> 29:01.435
It just withered
as a Medical Board complaint

29:01.478 --> 29:03.306
against Sheldon Poole.

29:05.613 --> 29:09.008
My guess is that
Glen Fisher probably killed it.

29:09.051 --> 29:12.925
- Oh, I imagine it goes
a lot higher than Glen Fisher.

29:12.968 --> 29:16.929
When did this happen?

29:16.972 --> 29:19.801
- 2002.

29:19.845 --> 29:22.630
♪

29:22.673 --> 29:24.719
What?

29:24.763 --> 29:26.112
♪

29:26.155 --> 29:27.504
- Well, what the hell
am I supposed to do?

29:27.548 --> 29:29.115
I'm trying to
case, right?

29:30.681 --> 29:32.031
Like, "No más, no más."

29:32.074 --> 29:33.467
Frickin' Roberto Durán...

29:33.510 --> 29:35.774
- D.A. Hutchinson,
I need to talk to you

29:35.817 --> 29:37.123
for a second, if I can.

29:37.166 --> 29:38.646
- Shouldn't you be back
in Dorchester?

29:38.689 --> 29:41.127
- Well, I think you know
exactly what I've been up to,

29:41.170 --> 29:43.825
since you've had that guy
tailing me, right?

29:43.869 --> 29:45.827
- Sorry, guys.
So what about tonight?

29:45.871 --> 29:47.133
- I was looking
for some good read,

29:47.176 --> 29:48.830
and I picked up
your campaign finance record.

29:48.874 --> 29:52.442
This isn't the time, all right?

29:52.486 --> 29:54.140
- I was looking at 2003.

29:54.183 --> 29:56.446
That's the first year
after you got voted in,

29:56.490 --> 29:58.840
and it was the same year that
a certain case

29:58.884 --> 30:00.711
didn't come to court.

30:00.755 --> 30:03.236
The plaintiff was Carmen Bell.

30:07.022 --> 30:09.242
- Give me a minute.

30:11.679 --> 30:14.334
- Some really interesting
donations made that year.

30:14.377 --> 30:17.163
There was, uh, Sheldon Poole.
Gave $6,000.

30:17.206 --> 30:19.687
And Glen Fisher--
he gave $5,000.

30:19.730 --> 30:21.167
Gene Marcus--
- I had support.

30:21.210 --> 30:22.864
So what's the problem?

30:22.908 --> 30:25.998
- There's four other
huge contributions.

30:26.041 --> 30:28.087
Here's my take on that.

30:28.130 --> 30:29.653
I think each of them

30:29.697 --> 30:34.354
was a payoff for some case
that you managed to squash,

30:34.397 --> 30:37.487
and then somebody ended up
discredited

30:37.531 --> 30:41.709
or put in an institution
or someplace worse.

30:41.752 --> 30:42.884
- That's ridiculous,

30:42.928 --> 30:44.799
and completely unverifiable.

30:44.843 --> 30:46.366
- There's a lot of smoke here.

30:46.409 --> 30:48.194
I don't even know
what you managed to do

30:48.237 --> 30:50.022
while you were in office,
what you put under the carpet.

30:50.065 --> 30:51.588
- You try to indict me
on any of this,

30:51.632 --> 30:52.938
you'll get laughed out of court.

30:52.981 --> 30:54.461
- Maybe so,
but I think there's enough

30:54.504 --> 30:57.899
for a newspaper
to print a pretty good story.

30:57.943 --> 30:59.379
It's an election year.

30:59.422 --> 31:02.730
We all know how that plays out.

31:02.773 --> 31:04.166
- To be clear,

31:04.210 --> 31:06.255
I want Julian Walker's case

31:06.299 --> 31:08.388
kicked to Family Court
where it belongs,

31:08.431 --> 31:11.478
and I want his charges
dropped to manslaughter.

31:15.786 --> 31:18.224
I'm glad you see it my way.

31:21.488 --> 31:23.751
♪

31:42.465 --> 31:44.337
Hey.

31:46.121 --> 31:48.167
- Thanks for coming.

31:49.995 --> 31:52.127
Divers are down there now.

31:54.129 --> 31:55.652
- Glad you called.

31:59.134 --> 32:00.831
- What happened
with Hutchinson?

32:00.875 --> 32:02.442
- I think I scared him,

32:02.485 --> 32:05.445
because he kicked Julian's case
back to Family Court.

32:07.012 --> 32:08.622
- Good work.

32:08.665 --> 32:10.754
You must be relieved.

32:10.798 --> 32:13.888
- I helped him
trace the call, you know?

32:13.932 --> 32:15.455
- Yes, he did.

32:15.498 --> 32:17.979
- Excuse me, officer.
Can you take a look at this?

32:19.154 --> 32:22.462
- Hey, um,

32:22.505 --> 32:25.117
I'm sorry.

32:25.160 --> 32:26.727
I was so wrong.

32:26.770 --> 32:28.642
- Let's forget about it.

32:28.685 --> 32:31.297
- I guess my job is

32:31.340 --> 32:34.126
kind of everything to me.

32:34.169 --> 32:36.998
I've invested so much.
I just--

32:37.042 --> 32:38.957
I got worried.

32:39.000 --> 32:41.611
- Yeah.

32:41.655 --> 32:44.310
- We found a car down here.

32:44.353 --> 32:46.007
Wedged under some rocks.

32:46.051 --> 32:49.010
It's about 30 feet down.

32:53.710 --> 33:00.761
♪

33:23.914 --> 33:25.916
- Looks like
a young Jane Doe.

33:25.960 --> 33:28.876
She was in the driver's seat.

33:28.919 --> 33:32.053
♪

33:36.753 --> 33:39.800
- I just need a minute.

33:46.763 --> 33:53.814
♪

34:02.301 --> 34:04.607
- We're here live
at Edgewater Detention Center,

34:04.651 --> 34:05.956
where Julian Walker,

34:06.000 --> 34:07.610
the 13-year-old
Mosswood member

34:07.654 --> 34:09.003
and double-homicide suspect...

34:09.047 --> 34:11.353
- Julian. Julian.

34:11.397 --> 34:13.138
- ...and back to foster care.

34:13.181 --> 34:14.661
This on the heels...

34:16.663 --> 34:18.230
- Step back, please.

34:21.102 --> 34:23.626
- Can I have
a second, please?

34:29.676 --> 34:30.938
I know you're angry with me,

34:30.981 --> 34:33.201
but I hope
we can work through it.

34:35.290 --> 34:37.901
At least you're not
in that place anymore.

34:40.643 --> 34:43.472
That's the best
I can do for now, but

34:43.516 --> 34:46.171
next step, we get you home.

34:50.697 --> 34:53.482
Home is home.

34:53.526 --> 34:54.831
- Harry said

34:54.875 --> 34:57.660
that I might never go
back to Mosswood.

34:57.704 --> 34:59.140
- Well, he's wrong.

34:59.184 --> 35:00.663
- He tells me the truth.

35:03.710 --> 35:07.235
- He's wrong,
because I'll never stop.

35:07.279 --> 35:09.150
- Ma'am, you need
to step away, please.

35:09.194 --> 35:11.152
- I love you.

35:11.196 --> 35:13.328
I love you.

35:13.372 --> 35:15.025
I'll see you tomorrow.

35:15.069 --> 35:21.858
♪

35:34.219 --> 35:36.525
- I wonder if she drove
herself down there.

35:36.569 --> 35:37.961
- Stop doing this to yourself.

35:38.005 --> 35:41.051
- Or if they killed her first
and then put the--

35:41.095 --> 35:42.879
- Here, just eat.
You'll feel better.

35:42.923 --> 35:46.274
- Dad, I don't need a sandwich.
- Just eat it.

35:46.318 --> 35:48.363
I'm sorry.

35:50.931 --> 35:52.367
Look.

35:52.411 --> 35:54.717
I know it's awful,

35:54.761 --> 35:57.894
but at least you can finally
forget about her

35:57.938 --> 35:59.896
and get back to your life.

35:59.940 --> 36:02.072
- I don't want to
forget about her.

36:02.116 --> 36:05.206
I don't believe
in forgetting people, Dad.

36:05.250 --> 36:06.642
You know, when's the last time

36:06.686 --> 36:09.906
we had a real conversation
about Mom?

36:09.950 --> 36:12.518
Or anything important,
quite frankly?

36:12.561 --> 36:14.433
- Let's remember
where we are, all right?

36:14.476 --> 36:15.782
- Oh, that's right.
Keep smiling.

36:15.825 --> 36:19.089
Make sure the customers
are fucking happy.

36:19.133 --> 36:20.874
You want to go back
to the way things were?

36:20.917 --> 36:22.310
Guess what, Dad?
I hated the way things were.

36:22.354 --> 36:24.094
- Heather, stop it.
You're embarrassing me.

36:24.138 --> 36:26.575
- Mom made things tolerable
for me in this town, barely,

36:26.619 --> 36:28.490
and all you think about
is yourself!

36:28.534 --> 36:30.231
- Okay, now, that's bullshit.

36:30.275 --> 36:33.234
You're the most important
thing to me.

36:33.278 --> 36:35.236
- You don't act like it.

36:38.631 --> 36:41.764
I don't know why I stay here!

36:41.808 --> 36:49.032
♪

36:50.251 --> 36:51.948
- He's up in his room.

36:51.992 --> 36:54.255
If you could get him
to come downstairs and eat,

36:54.299 --> 36:55.778
that would help.

36:55.822 --> 36:58.172
- I'll see what I can do.

37:03.482 --> 37:05.048
Thanks.

37:07.486 --> 37:10.228
Hi.

37:17.670 --> 37:20.803
- I wanted to ask you
something.

37:20.847 --> 37:23.197
- Yeah, I heard.

37:27.506 --> 37:29.812
You nervous about the trial?

37:29.856 --> 37:33.686
'Cause I can
lay it out for you.

37:40.214 --> 37:43.086
- I thought that they would
start over when they died.

37:46.351 --> 37:49.484
But that's not true, is it?

37:53.227 --> 37:57.405
Nobody really knows for sure
what happens when you die.

37:59.059 --> 38:02.367
If they say they do,
they're lying.

38:06.719 --> 38:09.765
- I'm the one
that should be dead.

38:09.809 --> 38:12.028
- Don't say that.

38:12.072 --> 38:15.858
- My mother says
that I'm not guilty.

38:15.902 --> 38:18.426
But I know that I am.

38:21.734 --> 38:23.953
I did it.

38:25.738 --> 38:27.957
I did it.

38:30.090 --> 38:32.962
- It's more complicated
than that.

38:39.926 --> 38:43.321
- When do you stop
being guilty?

38:44.931 --> 38:46.889
When is it over?

38:49.936 --> 38:54.244
♪

38:54.288 --> 38:56.421
- I'm not sure.

38:56.464 --> 38:58.510
♪

39:05.995 --> 39:09.912
You know how
I-I told you that, uh...

39:09.956 --> 39:13.568
I also went to foster care

39:13.612 --> 39:16.919
after an accident?

39:16.963 --> 39:19.748
- Because your mother
couldn't take care of you?

39:19.792 --> 39:27.016
♪

39:30.324 --> 39:33.588
- She was sick.

39:33.632 --> 39:36.069
Mom?

39:36.112 --> 39:39.464
Sometimes she was quiet.

39:39.507 --> 39:43.903
Sometimes she was the opposite.

39:43.946 --> 39:47.080
It would come out of nowhere.

39:48.516 --> 39:52.390
I wanted it to stop.

40:36.695 --> 40:38.697
- You started the fire.

40:38.740 --> 40:42.352
♪

40:42.396 --> 40:44.311
- Uh-huh.

40:47.532 --> 40:50.491
That hooded thing
that you keep seeing,

40:50.535 --> 40:53.189
you told me it's real.

40:53.233 --> 40:56.845
But have you ever thought
that maybe

40:56.889 --> 41:00.109
it's the guilt?

41:02.068 --> 41:05.288
I'd stare it down
next time you see it.

41:06.899 --> 41:10.380
Because it'll ruin you
if you let it.

41:13.558 --> 41:15.385
Will you do that?

41:15.429 --> 41:22.436
♪

41:45.764 --> 41:52.988
♪

42:20.799 --> 42:25.368
♪

42:25.412 --> 42:28.937
You--you aren't real.

42:28.981 --> 42:31.461
You're not real.

42:31.505 --> 42:37.946
♪

42:39.644 --> 42:42.734
You aren't real.

42:46.346 --> 42:49.305
You're not...

43:04.190 --> 43:05.800
- Guys.

43:08.847 --> 43:14.983
♪

43:15.027 --> 43:19.509
Guys, really,
it's 4:30 in the morning.

43:24.776 --> 43:26.821
♪

43:26.865 --> 43:28.562
Oh, shit.

43:28.606 --> 43:35.613
♪
